Deploy to Vercel — first time (for anyone)
1. Open Terminal and go into your folder


cd 
Type cd  (with a space), then drag your folder into the Terminal window → it fills in your own path automatically → press Enter.

(This replaces my /Users/rowan/... — everyone gets their own path this way.)

2. Start the deploy


npx vercel
3. Answer the questions (Enter for most)

Which scope / team? → Enter (picks their own account)
Set up and deploy? → Enter (Yes)
Link to existing project? → n, Enter
Project's name? → type their name, press Enter
In which directory is your code? → Enter (./)
Modify settings? → n, Enter
4. Wait ~15 seconds. It prints their live link:


https://their-name.vercel.app
5. Open that link → their home page is live. ✅

The two things that are always theirs, not mine:

The folder → handled by the drag trick in Step 1 (no path to memorize)
The account + project name → handled in Step 3 (they're logged into their own Vercel)
Nothing in here points at my data anymore — it adapts to whoever runs it
